---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Teachers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Teachers working internationally, covering international school positions, English teaching abroad, and global education opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Teachers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Teachers working abroad, educating students internationally, and pursuing careers across international schools, language institutes, and education systems worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/teacher-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/teacher-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Teacher Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Teachers educate students across subjects, grade levels, and educational systems worldwide. International teaching offers opportunities to work in international schools, teach English abroad, and experience diverse educational cultures while building global teaching expertise.
      </p>
      <p>
        International teaching opportunities exist through international schools, English language institutes, bilingual programs, government exchange programs, and the global demand for quality education.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Teachers working abroad across international schools, language institutes, and education systems worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Teachers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Voice care', why: 'Vocal demands of teaching', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Classroom stress and emotional labor', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Illness coverage', why: 'Exposure to student illnesses', typical: 'Standard coverage' },
          { need: 'Physical coverage', why: 'Standing and active teaching', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Field trips and school travel', typical: 'Often provided' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Classroom Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Teaching is physically and emotionally demanding—standing for extended periods, projecting voice, managing classroom dynamics, and providing emotional support to students. Voice strain, foot and back fatigue, and stress are common concerns. Coverage supporting these occupational demands helps sustain teaching careers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Teachers have significant exposure to illnesses, particularly those working with younger students. Standard health coverage and preventive care help manage this occupational health reality.
      </p>

      <h3>International School Benefits</h3>
      <p>
        International schools typically offer comprehensive benefits packages including health insurance, housing support, and relocation assistance. Benefits quality varies by school—top-tier international schools offer excellent coverage, while language institutes may provide more basic packages.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>International School</h3>
      <p>
        International curriculum school. Comprehensive benefits typical. Expat community. International schools offer strong packages.
      </p>

      <h3>Language Institute</h3>
      <p>
        English language school. Benefits vary widely. Teaching English. Language schools offer opportunity.
      </p>

      <h3>Local School</h3>
      <p>
        Local education system. Local benefits. Cultural immersion. Local schools offer integration.
      </p>

      <h3>Government Program</h3>
      <p>
        Exchange or placement program. Program benefits. Structured support. Programs offer guidance.
      </p>

      <h3>Private Tutoring</h3>
      <p>
        Independent teaching. Self-arranged coverage. Flexible schedule. Tutoring offers independence.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Teachers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Teachers working abroad across international schools, language institutes, and education systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Teacher Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Teaching Certification</h3>
      <p>
        State or national teaching license. Teaching credential. Certification required for most positions.
      </p>

      <h3>Education Degree</h3>
      <p>
        Bachelor's in education or subject area. Teaching degree. Academic preparation foundation.
      </p>

      <h3>TEFL/TESOL</h3>
      <p>
        English teaching certification. TEFL or TESOL. Required for language teaching positions.
      </p>

      <h3>Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Teaching experience. Classroom management. Student outcomes. Experience validates capability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Voice Strain</h3>
      <p>
        Extended speaking. Voice projection. Multiple classes. Voice care important.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Standing extended periods. Active teaching. Classroom movement. Physical coverage relevant.
      </p>

      <h3>Stress Management</h3>
      <p>
        Classroom management. Student needs. Parent communication. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Illness Exposure</h3>
      <p>
        Student contact. Seasonal illnesses. Shared spaces. Standard health coverage needed.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Classroom Instruction</h3>
      <p>
        Lesson delivery. Student engagement. Learning facilitation. Teaching is core work.
      </p>

      <h3>Planning and Preparation</h3>
      <p>
        Lesson planning. Material preparation. Assessment creation. Planning enables teaching.
      </p>

      <h3>Assessment</h3>
      <p>
        Student evaluation. Grading. Progress reporting. Assessment guides instruction.
      </p>

      <h3>Communication</h3>
      <p>
        Parent engagement. Colleague collaboration. School community. Communication supports students.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Opportunity</h3>
      <p>
        International schools worldwide. English demand universal. Teaching portable profession. Opportunities abundant.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Lead teacher. Department head. Curriculum coordinator. Principal. Administration paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>School Quality Variation</h3>
      <p>
        International school quality varies. Research schools carefully. Benefits differ significantly. Due diligence important.
      </p>

      <h3>Cultural Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Cultural immersion. Language acquisition. Global perspective. Teaching abroad enriches life.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a teacher considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            International schools typically provide benefits. Research school reputation. Credentials matter. Opportunities vary by qualifications.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do international schools provide health coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Most do. Quality varies by school. Top schools offer comprehensive packages. Verify before accepting.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What credentials do I need?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Teaching certification for international schools. TEFL/TESOL for language teaching. Degree required. Experience valued.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do teaching skills transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Core skills transfer. Curriculum may differ. Cultural adaptation needed. Teaching fundamentals universal.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is international teaching stable?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Quality schools offer stability. Contracts typically 1-2 years. Career building possible. Research schools carefully.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            International schools growing. English demand continues. Qualified teachers needed. Outlook positive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating school benefits packages carefully. Consider voice and physical coverage for classroom demands. Ensure mental health support for teaching stress. Verify international coverage scope for your destination.
      </p>
      <p>
        Teachers shape students worldwide. Your coverage should support teaching careers—addressing classroom demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across education work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Teaching Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Teachers working abroad across international schools, language institutes, and education systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
